ellon’s neal on funding liquidity and collateral back to top you must be signed in to use this feature sign in   hedgez fund profile northlight european fundamental credit fund fund investment objectives the fund is a longshort high yield credit fund with a directional bias the funds objective is to generate attractive liquidity adjusted absolute returns with an emphasis on risk management and capital preservation the investment manager uses extensive bottomup fundamental analysis to identify opportunities with an attractive risk return profile research is carried out by an inhouse team of analysts who make use of proprietary and third party research to build financial models and formulate investment recommendations market analysis contributes to determining an instruments relative value pricing trends and liquidity risk the fund will typically invest in the secured and unsecured bonds and loans of subinvestment grade companies which derive a substantial part of their revenues from activities in europe or whose capital structure instruments in part or in total trade in europe these instruments may be listed or unlisted and may or may not be rated capital is allocated to high conviction investments through long short event relative value and trading strategies market veterans launch european credit fund  hedgeweek contact about us  media ad guidelines cookies login register sign up for free newsletter operational resource centre technology resource centre market trends news special reports directory guides events training jobs awards homenewsarticles and features   tweet tweet market veterans launch european credit fund tue    tags  articles and features a team of credit market veterans from goldman sachs lehman brothers and glg partners have launched the northlight european fundamental credit fund longshort credit fund the team behind the fund have worked together previously and have a strong record in credit investments trading and of managing funds with similar strategies cyril armleder and charleshenri lorthioir worked at goldman sachs and then at glg partners in the capacity of comanager and credit research analyst for the credit fund and various longshort credit event driven and special situations portfolios in excess of usdbn shahar zer spent ten years at lehman brothers where he headed the leveraged loan trading desk and helped build out the european high yield platform the caymanbased northlight european fundamental credit fund mainly focuses on high yield investment opportunities in europe the team believes that the european high yield market is poised for significant growth over the next five years this is driven by capital constrained banks reducing their lending the continued closure of securitisation markets and companies’ desire to diversify their funding sources the fund employs a waynav mechanism which deals in a bid mid and offer nav struck independently by citco fund services using market prices the fund deals monthly on a bid nav for the outflow and the offer nav for the inflow and allows matching inflows and outflows at the traditional mid nav dan page managing director of brt’s business development says “the global economic events of  triggered a global paradigm shift in the funds industry many managers have taken steps to beef up their corporate governance and operational infrastructure however while many existing managers have battled outmoded infrastructure and reorganisation the door has been opened wide for new managers and platforms to explore a blank sheet approach to operating in the new paradigm “northlight is one such company it has worked with brt citco jpmorgan and kpmg to address the issues of investor alignment manager to investor alignment risk control and transparency at the same time it has retained an operational structure than enables it to fulfil its investment objectives and deliver in its alphagenerating sphere” the minimum initial investment is eur and the minimum subsequent investment is eur like this article  get the free daily newsletter print email furtherreading from hedgeweek best wishes for  from the global fund media team fri    best wishes for  from the global fund media team wed    hedgeweek usa awards  – last chance to vote thu    hedgeweek global awards  – voting now closed thu    gottex reports positive performance for alternative and multiasset product lines tue    from our other sites low rates and new regulations keep market conditions challenging says greenwich associates wed    beringea’s portfolio company abzena raises gbpm through aim listing wed    changes to barclays ofi steelpath midstream mlp index tue    ccp closes usdm healthcare pe fund tue    powershares canada adds two etfs to smart beta line tue    features guides  guide to setting up an alternative investment fund in europe wed   blogs building investment fund structures  from startup to stardom tue   before you head to the beach… fri   the cftc provides more robust protection to whistleblowers wed   awards hedgeweek global awards  thu   special reports cybersecurity in europe  wed   mitigating compliance risk for pe managers thu   sei blockchain  building ecosystems in financial services fri   mifid ii meeting the compliance challenge sat   investment opportunities in infrastructure debt thu   events total alts thursday september     catalyst cap intro ls equity  event driven investing monday september     intralinks insights briefing  lp survey thursday september     altso’s th annual rocktoberfest thursday october     mining investment middle east and central asia  monday october     all events training international trade finance – dubai sun   international securities settlements  custodial services  dubai tue   emir fri   international payments mon   strategic corporate governance  kuwait tue   all courses listingsdirectory augentius thu   ikonic fund services ltd tue   backstop solutions group tue   the gemini companies mon   fundcount llc tue   more directo